x4freetext: - By authors. Unfortunately, the data published in
tabular form in the paper for the 170 scattering angle
have a bias.  The data for 170 degree included below
are anyway the right.
Self-supporting foils of approximately 20 mugramm/
cm**2 natural boron were used as target.
The proton energy loss in the target ranged from about
7 to 2 KeV.

x4codes.hlp: Universita degli Studi di Firenze + INFN Firenze, Italy

x4freetext: Fifteen Si detectors were placed at backward angles
from 100 to 170 degrees in step 5 degrees; they were
cooled at liquid nitrogen.
Proton beam currents were in the range 100-200
nanoampere.

x4freetext: In general, our cross section curves agree well in
shape with the other data, and the absolute values are
in good agreement wiyh those from Symons+ and from
Segel+. However, some dicrepancies occur: data at 155
degrees are about 15% higher than those from Tautfest+
and data at 165 degrees are about 18% higher than the
ones from Mayer+. It should be noted that these
discrepancies are essentially systematic, even though
there is not well-defined trend. - All the comments by
authors.
